* indirect_dispatch.sno
* Bottleneck: $ (indirect) dynamic function dispatch — no compile cost.
* Contrast with eval_fixed.sno: $ is pure runtime lookup, much cheaper.
* 500 iterations of $FN(X) where FN = 'ADD1'.
    &TRIM = 1
    DEFINE('ADD1(V)')                   :(ADD1END)
ADD1    ADD1 = V + 1                    :(RETURN)
ADD1END
    FN = 'ADD1'
    X = 5
    N = 0
LOOP    N = LT(N, 500) N + 1           :F(DONE)
    R = $FN(X)
    :(LOOP)
DONE    OUTPUT = R
END
